{"id":"694007d997899389f0c82e9d","title":"Til Love Do Us Lie","origin_name":"Til Love Do Us Lie","slug":"til-love-do-us-lie","thumb":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/gotvtop102/goimg102@main/public/thumbs/ti/til-love-do-us-lie.webp","poster":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/gotvtop102/goimg102@main/public/posters/ti/til-love-do-us-lie.webp","year":"2011","type":"series","genre":[{"name":"Gia Đình","slug":"gia-dinh"},{"name":"Chính kịch","slug":"chinh-kich"}],"country":[{"name":"Trung Quốc","slug":"trung-quoc"},{"name":"Hồng Kông","slug":"hong-kong"}],"lang_key":"Thuyết Minh","episode_current":"Hoàn Tất(136/136)","quality":"HD","modified":"2025-12-17T16:13:09.000Z","is_4k":false,"is_exclusive":false,"status":"completed","showtimes":"","chieurap":false,"sub_docquyen":false,"episodes":[],"description":"<p>Career woman KAN YIK-PO (Sheung Tin Ngor) turns housewife unwillingly with the sudden resignation of her domestic helper. Being the only breadwinner in the family and faced with a restructuring at work, her husband, SUEN KA-ON (Cheung Siu Fai), finds himself on the verge of a mid-life crisis. PO’s younger sister, KAN YIK-TAN (Joyce Tang), is a devil-may-care woman. The fact that she has recently broken up with her boyfriend does not discourage her from starting another relationship. Quite the contrary, she marries Malaysian Chinese NG LOK-YAN (Hanjin Tan), a guy she merely knows about, and takes him back to Hong Kong. Come and see how intriguing and fun living in a household with culture shock under the same roof can be!</p>","tmdb_id":41967,"cast":["Trương Triệu Huy","Thương Thiên Nga","Đặng Lệ Minh","Tan Hanjin","Thang Doanh Doanh","Lâm Hạ Vy","Viên Vỹ Hào","Susan Tse Suet-Sum","Bowie Wu","Rachel Poon Siu-Tung","Suet Nei","Charmaine Li","Wong Ching","Lý Gia Thanh","Eddie Li Yu-Yeung"],"director":[],"keywords":[],"cast_meta":[{"name":"Trương Triệu Huy","name_vi":"Trương Triệu Huy","name_original":"Eddie Cheung Siu-Fai","tmdb_id":72732,"profile":"https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w5